  "prompt": "How do you jump to a certain page of a PDF file on the iPhone?",
  "response": "Jumping to a specific page in a PDF file on an iPhone is straightforward. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n### Using the **Books** App:\n1. **Open the PDF**: Launch the **Books** app and select the PDF you want to view.\n2. **Access the Page Navigator**: Tap the **screen** to bring up the controls.\n3. **Jump to a Page**: At the bottom, you\u2019ll see a **page counter**. Tap on it, then enter the page number you want to go to and press **Go**.\n\n### Using the **Files** App:\n1. **Open the PDF**: Navigate to the PDF file in the **Files** app and open it.\n2. **Access the Pages View**: Tap the **three dots** (...) or **square icon** (depending on the app version) to view thumbnails of all pages.\n3. **Select the Page**: Scroll or search for the page you want and tap on it to jump there.\n\n### Using **Adobe Acrobat Reader** (or another PDF reader):\n1. **Open the PDF**: Launch the Adobe Acrobat Reader app and open the PDF file.\n2. **Use the Page Navigator**: Tap the **screen** to reveal the controls, then tap the **page number** at the bottom.\n3. **Enter the Page Number**: Type the page number you want to jump to and confirm.\n\nThese methods should help you quickly navigate to any page in a PDF on your iPhone.",
